name: natural gas liquids production | natural gas liquids | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/1968/documentation

This inventory represents the production of natural gas liquids (NGL) from unprocessed natural gas. Due to a lack of process-specific data, the  dataset for drying, natural gas is used as a proxy. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.

The activity starts with the reception of natural gas, unprocessed in the NGL production plant

The activity ends with the processing of natural gas and the production of NGLs.
category: D:Electricity, gas, steam and air conditioning supply/35:Electricity, gas, steam and air conditioning supply/352:Manufacture of gas; distribution of gaseous fuels through mains/3520:Manufacture of gas; distribution of gaseous fuels through mains

processDocumentation.timeDescription: based on dataset drying, natural gas
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: based on dataset drying, natural gas
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Most extracted natural gas contains Natural Gas Liquids (NGL) to varying degrees. The NGL are separated through fractionation and it is a mixture of ethane, propane, butane, pentanes and natural gasoline in differing relative amounts. The process occurs in stages as the gas steam rises through several towers where heating units raise the temperature of the stream, causing the various liquids to separate and exit into specific holding tanks.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: Emissions are copied from dataset drying, natural gas. Original flow refered to 1 m3 natural gas after the drying process (Emmenegger, 2007). This has been recalculated to fit the input amount of natural gas.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: inventory based on dataset drying, natural gas
